You can solve this in muplitple way, just alternative one for fun.
Use array of 26 to count freq of every char in "chars".
Then iterate over array of words and for each one start counting freq of chars in that word. Every time we count one char in a word compare if that char count is no more than a count of the same char in "chars". If greater - this word cannnot be count. Otherwise in the end add length of the word to result.

O(NxM) time - need to check every char in every word in words. O(1) space (we use arrays of length 26)

```
    public int countCharacters(String[] words, String chars) {
        if (chars == null || chars.isEmpty() || words == null || words.length == 0)
            return 0;

        int[] counts = new int[26];
        for (char ch : chars.toCharArray()) {
            ++counts[ch - 'a'];    
        }

        int res = 0;
        for (String w : words) {
            int[] wordCounts = new int[26];
            boolean possible = true;
            for (char ch : w.toCharArray()) {
                int idx = ch - 'a';
                ++wordCounts[idx];
                if (wordCounts[idx] > counts[idx]) {
                    possible = false;
                    break;
                }
            }

            if (!possible)
                continue;

            res+=w.length();
        }
        return res;
    }
```

