# Code
```
/*
Algorithm - 
1. Initialize the count to 0. 
2. Iterate through an array of strings. 
    - Check if the string element at index, i is good with the string, chars. 
        - If it is good, increment the count by the length of the string, words[i]. 
3. Return the value of the count variable onto the main method. 

Helper Function isGood - 
1. Create a hashmap to map the characters in string, chars to the occurrence by iterating through the string, chars. 
2. Check the elements of hashmap and its occurrence before modification. 
3. Iterate through the string word and check if the character, ch exists in the hashmap and its occurrence is greater than 0, 
if it is then decrement the occurrence of that character by 1 and assign the new value to the key (i.e, character ch) onto the hashmap, hm. 
Else, return false if the character is not present in the hashmap or the count of the character is equal to 0. 
4. Verify the hashmap after modification for error checks/testing. 
5. Return true onto the calling function if the string is good. 

Complexity Analysis - 
1. Time Complexity = O(N ^ 2 + N * M) => O(N ^ 2)
2. Space Complexity = O(N)

*/

class Solution {
    public int countCharacters(String[] words, String chars) {
        int count = 0;

        for (int i = 0; i < words.length; i++) {
            if (isGood(words[i], chars)) {
                System.out.println("Good");
                count += words[i].length();
            }
        }

        return count;
    }

    private boolean isGood(String word, String chars) {
        Map<Character, Integer> hm = new HashMap<>();

        for (int i = 0; i < chars.length(); i++) {
            char ch = chars.charAt(i);
            hm.put(ch, hm.getOrDefault(ch, 0) + 1);
        }
        System.out.println("Hashmap before modification  " + hm);

        for (int i = 0; i < word.length(); i++) {
            char ch = word.charAt(i);
            if (hm.containsKey(ch) && hm.get(ch) > 0) {
                hm.put(ch, hm.get(ch) - 1);
            } else {
                return false;
            }
        }
        System.out.println("Hashmap after modification " + hm);
        return true;
    }
}
```

