# Non Optimized solution 1:
Start from target index 0, and word index 0
- Check every word that has a matching character 
- if matching found, in the remaining target and words length, find the found and add them and return
```
class Solution {
    public int numWays(String[] words, String target) {
            if(target.length() == 0) return 0;
        return ways(words, target, 0, 0);
    }

    int ways(String[] words, String target, int t_index, int w_index){
        if(t_index == target.length()) return 1;
        int remaining = target.length() - t_index-1;
        int count = 0;
        for(int i=0; i<words.length; i++){
            String word = words[i];
            for(int j=w_index; j<word.length()-remaining; j++){
                if(word.charAt(j) == target.charAt(t_index)){
					// match found, find the match of remaining and count them all together
                    count += ways(words, target, t_index + 1, j+1);
                }
            }
        }
        return count;
    }

}
```

# Slightly Optimized Solution 2:
The above solution can be optimized by remembering the counts once they are calculated in a map or a matrix.
```
class Solution {
    public int numWays(String[] words, String target) {
            if(target.length() == 0) return 0;
        m = new Long[target.length()][words[0].length() ]; 
        return (int) ways(words, target, 0, 0);
    }

    Long[][] m ;
    long ways(String[] words, String target, int t_index, int w_index){
        if(t_index >= target.length()) return 1;
        if(w_index >= words[0].length() ) return 0;
        if(words[0].length() - w_index < target.length()-t_index) return 0;

        if(m[t_index][w_index] != null) return m[t_index][w_index];

        int remaining = target.length() - t_index-1;
        long count = 0;
        for(int i=0; i<words.length; i++){
            String word = words[i];
            for(int j=w_index; j<word.length()-remaining; j++){
                if(word.charAt(j) == target.charAt(t_index)){
                    count += ways(words, target, t_index + 1, j+1);
                }
            }
        }
        m[t_index][w_index] = count%1000000007;
        return m[t_index][w_index];
    }

}
```
