# Intuition
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->
Once an index is visited we cannot pick any character behind that index. So keeping a track of the character that is required and the frequency of that character at a given index ,we can find a recursive solution to solve the problem.

# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
Recursion + DP

# Complexity
- Time complexity: O(N*N)
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->


- Space complexity: O(N*N)
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->


# Code
```
class Solution {
    static long dp[][];
    static long div=(long)1e9 +7;
    static int count[][];
    public static int numWays(String[] words, String target) {
        int n=target.length();
        int m=words[0].length();
        int m1=words.length;
        dp=new long[n][m];
        count=new int[m][26];
        for(int i=0;i<n;i++) for(int j=0;j<m;j++) dp[i][j]=-1;
        for(int i=0;i<m;i++){
            for(int j=0;j<m1;j++){
                count[i][words[j].charAt(i)-'a']++;
            }
        }
        return (int)func(target,words,0,0);
    }
    public static long func(String target,String words[],int ind1,int ind2)
    {
        int n=target.length();
        int m=words[0].length();
        if(m-ind2<n-ind1) return 0;
        if(ind1>=n) return 1;
        if(ind2>=m) return 0;
        if(dp[ind1][ind2]!=-1) return dp[ind1][ind2];
        long k1=0;
        long c=count[ind2][target.charAt(ind1)-'a'];
        if(c!=0) k1+=((c%div)*(func(target,words,ind1+1,ind2+1))%div)%div;
        k1+=func(target,words,ind1,ind2+1)%div;
        return dp[ind1][ind2]=k1%div;
    }
}
```

