// Startegy - Bottom Up solution
// My dp[i] array holds the MAX num of ways to form a string of length 'i'

// How DP is filled ?
// NOTE : ALL the word in words[] are of same length so we can know that freq[i-th char] from ALL the word's i-th char (if there are 5 words and 3 words have 'a' at index 0 and 2 words ahve 'b' at index 0 so ---> freq[] array which corresponds to i-th index of words would show a freq of 3 for 'a' and 2 for 'b' and 0 for rest)

// 1. At EACH INDEX of words, find the FREQ of EACH char -> So EACH index will have a corresponding int[26] array holding the freq of each char at 'i-th' idx
// 2. Once we have this, we try to FILL our DP
// OBSERVATION: At any moment, the MAX length of 'target' we can try to form is 'i' (since we know the freq of char at 'i', we can only try to find the number of ways to fill 'target' at index 'i' or less than 'i')
// 2.1 Because of above observation, the MAX 'j' which we can take anytime is 'i'
// 2.2 If j == 0, this means that there is NOTHING that has been formed yet (or tried to form), so MAX ways to form target(j) is freq[of char present at target(j)]
// 2.3 At anytime (j != 0), the TOTAL number of ways to FILL the char at index 'j' of target is 
// THE NUMBER of ways to fill 'j - 1' char (held in dp[j - 1]) * (multiply by) the FREQ of char at freq[] (basically, lets say freq[j] = 2 and dp[j - 1] = 4, so this means to form target upto 'j - 1' there are 4 ways and currently 2 different word from words[] has 'char' at curr location so 4 * 2 = 8)

// TC : O(M * N); M = words.length; N = words[0].length
// SC : O(N)
```
class Solution {
    public int numWays(String[] words, String target) {
        long dp[] = new long[target.length()]; // dp[i] means NUMBER of ways to form a string upto length 'i'
        long mod = 1000000000 + 7;

        for(int i = 0; i < words[0].length(); i++) { // since ALL words are of same length, i = idx in a word
            int[] freq = new int[26]; // freq of EACH char at 'i-th' idx from EACH word
            for(String word : words) {
                freq[word.charAt(i) - 'a']++; // for each idx, we know the freq of each char
            }

            // The max length we can take care at this time is 'i' (since we have freq of each char at 'i' and we already have dp[i - 1])
            for(int j = Math.min(i, target.length() - 1); j >= 0; j--) { // MAX we can fill upto now is until 'i-th' idx
                if(freq[target.charAt(j) - 'a'] > 0) { // we are trying to see if we can make 'target's index 'j'' from freq[]
                    // if the idx = 0, nothing has been formed yet so max ways to form target(j) = freq[target.charAt(j) - 'a']
                    // if j != 0, meaning we have previously found the MAX ways to find the dp[j - 1] so for dp[j] its just prev num of ways multiply by current freq
                    dp[j] += (j == 0) ? freq[target.charAt(j) - 'a'] : dp[j - 1] * freq[target.charAt(j) - 'a']; // we calculate dp[j] for every 'i' so keep adding to the answer (+=)
                    dp[j] %= mod; // we need to mod
                }
            }
        }
        return (int)dp[dp.length - 1];
    }
}
```

