# Intuition
Store all the character in map that provides info how much times this cahracter is seen before particular location (including)

# Approach
Write top-down and convert to bottom-up

# Complexity
- Time complexity:
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

- Space complexity:
O(nm)


m is length of word
n is length of target
k is length of words

# Code
```
class Solution {
    int[][] memo;
    int mod = 1000000007;
    long[][] countOfChars;
    int n,m;
    public int numWays(String[] words, String target) {
        n = target.length();
        m = words[0].length();
        countOfChars = new long[26][m];

        for(String w : words){
            for(int i = 0; i < w.length(); i++){
                countOfChars[w.charAt(i) - 'a'][i]++;
            }
        }

        memo = new int[n+1][m+1];
        Arrays.stream(memo).forEach(ar -> Arrays.fill(ar, -1));
        // return  countWays(words, target, n, m);
        return countWays(words, target);
    }

    public int countWays(String[] words, String target, int i, int takenSoFar){
        if(i == 0){
            return 1;
        }

        if(takenSoFar == 0){
            return 0;
        }

        if(memo[i][takenSoFar] != -1){
            return memo[i][takenSoFar];
        }


        char whatWeNeed = target.charAt(i-1);
        long ans = countWays(words, target, i, takenSoFar - 1) % mod;

        ans  += (countOfChars[whatWeNeed - 'a'][takenSoFar-1]   * countWays(words, target, i-1, takenSoFar - 1) ) % mod;



        return memo[i][takenSoFar] =  (int) ans % mod;
    }

// start with base case of recursion
     public int countWays(String[] words, String target){
        int n = target.length(), m = words[0].length();
        long[][] dp = new long[n+1][m+1]; // i - target char, j is word char
        Arrays.stream(dp).forEach(ar -> ar[0] = 0);
        Arrays.fill(dp[0], 1);


        for(int i = 1; i <= n; i++){
            for(int j = 1; j <= m; j++){
                dp[i][j] = dp[i][j-1] % mod;
                char whatWeNeed = target.charAt(i-1);

                dp[i][j] = (dp[i][j] + dp[i-1][j-1] * countOfChars[whatWeNeed - 'a'][j-1] ) % mod;
            }
        }


         return (int) dp[n][m];
    }
}
```

