Time Complexity: O(nlogn).
**STEPS:**
1. Sort the nums array.
2. Use two pointer approach. Place one pointer at the beginning and one at the end.
3. Put the smaller values on the odd index and larger on the even index till start is less than end.
4. Break the loop, now start and end are pointing to the same index.
5. Check whether the size of the nums is odd, if it is then add the nums[start] into the resultant array. 
6. Return the resultant array.  

