The idea is to convert the array in increasing and decreaing sequence (IDID... or DIDI....). 
Consider current i as I then i-1 and i+1 will be D. As i is greater than i-1 and i+1, average of i-1 and i+1 will always be less that i. Same will apply if i is D and i-1 and i+1 is I. In this case average of i-1 and i+1 will always be greater than i.

```class Solution {
    public int[] rearrangeArray(int[] nums) {
        boolean increasing = nums[1] > nums[0];
        for(int i = 1; i < nums.length-1; i++){
            if((increasing && nums[i+1] > nums[i]) || !increasing && nums[i+1] < nums[i]){
                swap(nums, i, i+1);
            }
            increasing = !increasing;
        }

        return nums;
    }

    private void swap(int[] arr, int x, int y){
        int temp = arr[x];
        arr[x] = arr[y];
        arr[y] = temp;
    }
}

