solutions.content:
The aim is to arrange the array such that the ```avg(nums[i-1],nums[i+1]) != nums[i]```.

One way to make it possible is to make every ```nums[i]``` 

	greater than both ```nums[i+1]``` and ```nums[i-1]``` Or smaller than both ```nums[i+1]``` and ```nums[i-1]```.

because in both the situations ```avg(nums[i-1],nums[i+1])``` will not be equal to ```nums[i]```.

To achieve this Sort the ```nums```array in increasing order, then add alternate greater and smaller element into ```ans``` array. i.e add one element from back and one element from front.

```
class Solution {
    public int[] rearrangeArray(int[] nums) {
        int[] ans = new int[nums.length];
        Arrays.sort(nums);

        for(int i=0,j=nums.length-1,k=0;i<=j;k++){
            ans[k] = (k&1)==0?nums[j--]:nums[i++];
        }
        return ans;
    }
}
```

