# Intuition
We need to rearrange the elements in the given array such that for every i:

nums[i-1] < nums[i] if i is odd.
nums[i-1] > nums[i] if i is even.

# Approach
To solve this problem, we can go through the input array and compare adjacent elements. If the element at index i violates the given conditions, we swap it. So that both neighbors are bigger then number at odd positoin `(leftItem > i(odd) < rightItem)`.
`(leftItem < i(even) > rightItem)`

# Complexity
- Time complexity:
O(n) where n is the size of the array.

- Space complexity:
O(1) because we are modifying the input array in place.

# Code
Python
```
class Solution:
    def rearrangeArray(self, nums: List[int]) -> List[int]:
        for i in range(1, len(nums)):
            if i % 2 == 1:
                if nums[i] < nums[i - 1]:
                    nums[i - 1], nums[i] = nums[i], nums[i-1]
            if i % 2 == 0:
                if nums[i] > nums[i - 1]:
                    nums[i - 1], nums[i] = nums[i], nums[i-1]
        return nums
```
