# Explanation
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->

- input : 6,2,0,9,7
- sort  : 0,2,6,7,9
- we would replace last bigger numbers and make it in between numbers.
- to make it one big number , then one small number _ , 7, _ , 9 , _ 
- select bigger numbers => (nums.Length / 2)
- then make pointer refers on the first bigger number
- int pointer = nums.Length / n; // 3
- the iterator should be increase by 2 every round

# Code
```
public class Solution {
    public int[] RearrangeArray(int[] nums) {
        Array.Sort(nums);

        int pointer = nums.Length - (nums.Length / 2);

        for (int i = 1; i < nums.Length; i+=2)
        {
            int temp = nums[i];
            nums[i] = nums[pointer];
            nums[pointer++] = temp;
        }
        return nums;
    }
}
```

